package org.drools.generated;

declare TaxPayer
    taxpayerId : String
    income : double
    taxRate : int
end

rule "Set Tax Rate 10%"
salience 100
when
    $tp : TaxPayer(income < 30000, taxRate == 0)
then
    modify($tp) { setTaxRate(10) }
end

rule "Set Tax Rate 22%"
salience 90
when
    $tp : TaxPayer(income >= 30000, income < 80000, taxRate == 0)
then
    modify($tp) { setTaxRate(22) }
end

rule "Set Tax Rate 32%"
salience 80
when
    $tp : TaxPayer(income >= 80000, taxRate == 0)
then
    modify($tp) { setTaxRate(32) }
end

This DRL code defines three rules to assign a tax rate based on the income of a taxpayer. The rules are mutually exclusive and use salience to ensure only one rule fires for each fact:

1. **Set Tax Rate 10%**: Applies when income is less than 30,000.
2. **Set Tax Rate 22%**: Applies when income is between 30,000 (inclusive) and 80,000 (exclusive).
3. **Set Tax Rate 32%**: Applies when income is 80,000 or more.

Each rule checks that `taxRate` is initially set to 0 to prevent re-firing once a tax rate has been assigned. The salience values ensure the rules are evaluated in order of priority, with higher numbers firing first.